⁠

node.text:
OM has been called the sound of God humming. 😌 It's more than a chant; it's a connection to consciousness... to the ego, to the intellect and mind, to the senses and finally to the physical body and material world. ⁠
⁠
In meditation, we use OM to journey inward to reconnect to our source of pure consciousness. ✨⁠
⁠
It's like returning hOMe. Join us in the Chopra App for our new series, "From OM to Home" with our Chief Meditation Officer, Roger Gabriel, to learn more about the power of OM, and how you can use it to becOMe who you're meant to be - link in bio.

node.text:
As with happiness, peace is an inside job. 💛  Peace feels like...⁠
⁠
🔹 Breezing through your initial anger in a situation that pushes your buttons⁠
🔹 Scrolling on by when you see something on social media you don't agree with⁠
🔹 Keeping your cool in conflict by responding with compassion rather than reacting from conditioning ⁠
⁠
Our favorite way to establish this kind of equanimity is meditation, which will train your brain to bring awareness to your thoughts, making space between reality and response. Train with us in the Chopra App, where you'll find over 500 meditations to get you started – link in bio.

node.text:
We often talk about letting things pass that are "heavy" or not "in flow," which are intuitive powers that can align us with our truth. On the flip side, they can also be misused to spiritually bypass difficult situations that could be worth it for our personal growth. So... should you go for it? You can ask yourself these questions to know if something is right for you:⁠
⁠
👉  1. Why is this difficult? If your self-limiting beliefs are holding you back from pursuing what you want, remember that the universe does not put a desire in your head that you can't fulfill. On the other hand, are you efforting to the point of personal sacrifice? If so, what are you willing to give up to fulfill this vision and when is it no longer serving you? ⁠
⁠
👉  2. What do I really, really want? Try inquiring during your meditation and see what comes up. Deep in your heart, you know what's best for you. We will ask people for advice just to remind us that we didn't need their input in the first place. Getting clear on what feels right in your body can inform the mind on an important decision.⁠
⁠
👉  3. If I say yes, will it be for the highest good - for me and everyone involved? Sometimes we need to take a step outside the details to look at the bigger picture. If you answer this one honestly, I think you know what to do. ⁠
⁠
📷  @poco.collective
